<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Streaming Search LTR — Netflix-style Demo</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/demo/ui/styles.css"/>
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar" id="navbar">
    <div class="nav-left">
      <div class="logo">STREAMING SEARCH LTR</div>

      <select id="profile">
        <option value="chrisen">Chrisen</option>
        <option value="gilbert">Gilbert</option>
      </select>

      <select id="language"></select>

      <div class="pills">
        <div class="pill">API: <b id="api">…</b></div>
        <div class="pill">Offline lift: <b id="lift">…</b></div>
        <div class="pill">Tip: click a tile → “Why this?” → Voice</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="nav-right">
      <input id="search" placeholder="Search… (type for suggestions)"/>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1 class="hero-title">Search + LTR + Agentic RAG</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Netflix-style discovery demo powered by your backend:
        <b>hybrid retrieval</b> → <b>LambdaRank rerank</b> → <b>grounded answer</b> → <b>agentic retry</b>.
        <br/>This is a demo (MovieLens metadata), not affiliated with any provider.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" id="refreshRows">▶ Refresh Rows</button>
        <button class="btn btn-secondary" id="whatIsThis">ℹ What am I seeing?</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="content" id="content"></main>

  <div class="modal" id="modal">
    <div class="modal-card">
      <div class="modal-head">
        <div>
          <div class="modal-title" id="mTitle">Title</div>
          <div class="small" id="mMeta"></div>
        </div>
        <button class="close" id="closeModal">×</button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <div class="actions">
          <button id="whyThis" class="primary">Why this?</button>
          <button id="whyThisAgent">Why this? (Agent)</button>
          <button id="speak">🔊 Speak</button>
          <button id="stop">■ Stop</button>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-grid">
          <div class="box">
            <h4>Synopsis</h4>
            <div class="small" id="mSynopsis">—</div>
          </div>

          <div class="box">
            <h4>Grounded explanation</h4>
            <div id="mExplain" class="small">—</div>
          </div>

          <div class="box">
            <h4>Sources</h4>
            <pre id="mSources">—</pre>
          </div>

          <div class="box">
            <h4>Debug</h4>
            <pre id="mDebug">—</pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <audio id="audio" controls style="width:100%;margin-top:14px;display:none"></audio>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="modal" id="infoModal">
    <div class="modal-card">
      <div class="modal-head">
        <div class="modal-title">What you’re seeing</div>
        <button class="close" id="closeInfo">×</button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <div class="box">
          <h4>Pipeline (clear + honest)</h4>
          <div class="small">
            <ol>
              <li><b>Retrieval</b>: BM25 + dense embedding search → merged hybrid candidates.</li>
              <li><b>LTR rerank</b>: LambdaRank model reranks the top candidates using retrieval features.</li>
              <li><b>Grounded RAG</b>: LLM is forced to answer only from retrieved snippets and cite sources.</li>
              <li><b>Agentic retry</b>: If the answer is unsupported / missing citations, the agent retries with adjusted retrieval.</li>
              <li><b>Offline lift</b>: Shows nDCG@10 improvement of hybrid_ltr over hybrid from your eval report.</li>
            </ol>
            <b>Important:</b> MovieLens doesn’t contain real Netflix-level metadata (language, trailers, etc).
            If you want “Tamil love story” to be real, you must add a catalog dataset with a language field.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script src="/demo/ui/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
